Ceres: "Even though I'm called the commander of the knights, I'm just

Ceres: "The decision-making power to move the Moduna army, also known

Ceres: "Well... they do listen to my opinion a bit... but still..."

\C[24][Becky]\C[0] "But Lord Ceres, you are married to Princess Alicia, aren't you? Then

Ceres: "You understand...?!"

Ceres: "Luna, you haven't changed at all since then. Straightforward,
serious, honest, kind... But can you really not forgive Lucia? You two
were so close."
Ceres: "I see."
Ceres: "Luna, I haven't changed my personality either, have I?"

\C[23][Luna]\C[0] "I think you have changed a little, Lord Ceres. You're different from

Ceres: "Is that so?"

\C[23][Luna]\C[0] I think the Lord Ceres of the past was more of a slacker. Compared to

Ceres: I see...!
\C[23][Luna]\C[0] Hehe...

\C[23][Luna]\C[0] Lord Ceres, why does the Knights of Messiah interfere with other

Ceres: ...
Ceres: ...

Ceres: It's for the sake of a man who wished for true peace without
resistance.
\C[23][Luna]\C[0] A man without resistance?

Ceres: The battle with Grales... During that war, various countries

Ceres: But a certain person from a certain country tried to break the
chain of wars. They said, "Let's all stop this endless war." And so,

Ceres: Naturally, the country that gave up fighting unilaterally
suffered damage. Even so, a certain man from that country persisted in

countrymen died.

Ceres: In the end, that man even made graves for the enemy soldiers
and protected the citizens of the enemy nation while only defending
against their attacks.

\C[23][Luna]\C[0] Is this man without resistance Prince Reanu of the Kingdom of

Ceres: ...

Ceres: Prince Reanu of Ryubel was once known as a skilled warrior who

Ceres: I asked Reanu many times. Why are you, of all people, just

Ceres: When I heard the answer from Reanu... when I heard 'the true

Ceres: Haha... Sorry, for such a boring and long-winded story. I just

Ceres: ...
Ceres: But... Reanu was wrong.

Ceres: Non-resistance doesn't work against opponents who won't listen
to reason.
Ceres: I couldn't do anything for Reanu. I was powerless.
\C[23][Luna]\C[0] Lord Ceres...
Ceres: ...

Ceres: It's sad, but perhaps Lucia has become one of those 'opponents

Ceres: But I'm holding onto a sliver of hope and thought about talking

Ceres: I don't have the power to move armies; I'm just a middle

Ceres: Moduna is a small country. It's not a nation that can voice its

Ceres: The little that I can do is to first head to Jupiterino and

Ceres: Who knows. They're quite capricious.
Ceres: Well then, I should be heading back soon.

Ceres: If I stay here alone with you, Luna, any longer, I might turn

\C[23][Luna]\C[0] What are you thinking? We were having a serious conversation... I'm
